HEADWORD: Machinator
<hw>Mach"i*na`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<def>One who machinates, or forms a scheme with evil designs; a plotter
or artful schemer.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill. Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
